The paper discusses the vulnerabilities of web password recovery systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also provides a framework for analyzing such systems, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of such systems, which involves issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper also discusses the user experience of password recovery systems, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
